ue\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 22, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104xnq1665702775708.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xnq1665702775708.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xnq1665702775708.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"xnq1665702775708\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Defines the behavior of the worksheet plug-in component when the IDE issues a request\n    to refresh the current main object editor.</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104xnq1665702775708_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"xnq1665702775708__codeblock_ccy_ktm_mzb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">operation ws_refresh\n ; &lt;... Your code here ...&gt;\nend; operation refresh </code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xnq1665702775708__section_rbj_mtm_mzb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d757654e54\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xnq1665702775708__p_d4700e1_d4701e1_d4702e1\">The IDE activates this operation when something in the\n        editor has changed that requires a refresh.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xnq1665702775708__p_d4703e1_d4704e1_d4705e1\">For example, if you have added a field in the Define\n        Structure worksheet, the IDE issues a refresh request to the editor's views, such as the\n        Property Inspector and worksheets, including the user-defined worksheet. The\n          <span class=\"keyword apiname\">ws_refresh</span> command enables you to respond to the refresh request\n        appropriately.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xnq1665702775708__p_d4706e1_d4707e1_d4708e1\">The operation is optional.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xnq1665702775708__section_xjp_gjr_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d757654e72\">Example</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xnq1665702775708__p_d4712e1_d4713e1_d4714e1\">For example, in a worksheet that generates statistics about\n        the current development object, the <span class=\"keyword apiname\">ws_refresh</span> operation could regenerate\n        the statistics by calling the appropriate operation:</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104xnq1665702775708_html_1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"xnq1665702775708__codeblock_yx4_4tm_mzb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">operation ws_refresh\n variables\n string vOutput\n endvariables\n $instancehandle-&gt;getStatistics($URL$, vOutput)\n return 0\nend ; ws_refresh</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533813\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533813\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "ws_refresh Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 22, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Defines the behavior of the worksheet plug-in component when the IDE issues a request to refresh the current main object editor. Explain this code operation ws_refresh ; <... Your code here ...> end; operation refresh Copy Description The IDE activates this operation when something in the editor has changed that requires a refresh. For example, if you have added a field in the Define Structure worksheet, the IDE issues a refresh request to the editor's views, such as the Property Inspector and worksheets, including the user-defined worksheet. The ws_refresh command enables you to respond to the refresh request appropriately. The operation is optional. Example For example, in a worksheet that generates statistics about the current development object, the ws_refresh operation could regenerate the statistics by calling the appropriate operation: Explain this code operation ws_refresh variables string vOutput endvariables $instancehandle->getStatistics($URL$, vOutput) return 0 end ; ws_refresh Copy Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}